patch.comment:
Work around an issue where GitHub Pages cannot render `

` inside a pipes-and-dashes table (even though GHFM supports this)
Support more API types for the markdown generator: namespace, function, type alias, variable
Update to work with refactored ApiModel classes
Update web site URLs
The YAML exporter now documents "extends" and "implements" heritage
Updated to use the new InternalError class for reporting software defects

major.comment: THIS IS A BETA RELEASE - We are bumping the version to "7.0.0" to simplify dogfooding. This release is not yet ready for general usage.

patch.comment: add uid to implements and extends blocks, fix uid references
Removing the OfficeYamlDocumenter logic to correct escape characters within code ticks
Fix issue where broken hyperlinks sometimes appear in docs.microsoft.com due to matching of IYamlItem.fullName
Update URLs in OfficeYamlDocumenter
Update "repository" field in package.json
Republish all packages in web-build-tools to resolve GitHub issue #782
render markdown for namespace; fix api ref check for namespace
Allow markdown to continue generating when api reference check failed
Updating OfficeYamlDocumenter to append snippets to non-empty sections

minor.comment: Add support for the "@eventproperty" AEDoc tag, which indicates that a class/interface property should be documented as an event

patch.comment: Changing Office's APIExtractor add-on to unescape characters in code blocks

minor.comment: The YAML target now automatically hyperlinks type references, but only if the type name is simple and not ambiguous

patch.comment: Improve OfficeYamlDocumenter to replace escaped function arrows in code lines with =>
Fix a issue where Office Documentation had markdown characters escaped

minor.comment: Add support for rendering the new IMarkupHtmlTag

patch.comment: The output folder is not automatically created if it doesn't exist yet
Update API Set URL resolution in OfficeYamlDocumenter

minor.comment: Add support for new AEDoc tags @sealed, @virtual, and @override

patch.comment: Change name and set href for TOC root node.
Refactor to use new @microsoft/node-core-library
Upgrade colors to version ~1.2.1
Change heading for code snippets section from `## Snippets` to `#### Examples`.
Customize the `API Set #.#` hyperlink target by host.
Designate proper language for each code snippet (TypeScript or JavaScript).
Fix an issue where GitHub changed its markdown parser such that "./" is now required for relative hyperlinks
Fix a bug where MarkdownRenderer did not handle newlines properly inside table cells
Improve appearance of warning messages
Locked down some "@types/" dependency versions to avoid upgrade conflicts
Force a patch bump in case the previous version was an empty package

patch.author: Nicholas Pape <nickpape-msft@users.noreply.github.com>
patch.comment: Update Jest to ~21.2.1

patch.author: QZ <qz2017@users.noreply.github.com>
patch.comment: lock the reference version between web build tools projects

patch.author: pgonzal <pgonzal@users.noreply.github.com>
patch.comment: Updated to work with the latest api-extractor
